
"What's wrong?" Jeff asks me, he reaches for my hand but I push him away.
"Nothing's wrong." I snap out of my fit of hysteria. "I'd like to go to sleep now." I tell him.
"Fine." He snaps. "Smile, show her the spare room. I'll be in bed." He stands up and walks into the dark hall. I hear a far door slam shut as the sound of his footsteps stop. Smile turns to me, nudges my leg and leads me to the back hall.